main_text: Chinese Chicken Corn SoupThis is a popular soup served in Chinese banquets in lieu of sharkâ€™s fin soup. Easy to make and yet so tasty.2 chicken ribs skinned3/4 lt waterSoup ingredients:1 tsp garlic grated1 tsp ginger grated1 medium size onion finely chopped1 tbsp chicken granules1/4 cup carrot finely cubed3/4 cup corn kernels fresh or frozen1/2 cup creamed cornSlurry/Seasoning:1 tbsp corn flour2 tbsp water3 eggs whisked1 tsp sesame oil1/4 tsp black pepperSalt to taste- Bring water and chicken to a boil lower fire to medium and simmer for 15 mins- Scoop put chicken and let it cool slightly before removing the bones shredding the meat- Add the soup ingredients to the stock and simmer on medium heat for further 15 mins. {"1": {"comment_id": "asiameltingpot"  "comment_text": "Chinese Chicken Corn Soup

This is a popular soup served in Chinese banquets in lieu of sharkâ€™s fin soup. Easy to make and yet so tasty.

2 chicken ribs  skinned
3/4 lt water

Soup ingredients:
1 tsp garlic  grated
1 tsp ginger  grated
1 medium size onion  finely chopped
1 tbsp chicken granules
1/4 cup carrot  finely cubed
3/4 cup corn kernels  fresh or frozen
1/2 cup creamed corn

Slurry/Seasoning:
1 tbsp corn flour
2 tbsp water
3 eggs  whisked
1 tsp sesame oil
1/4 tsp black pepper
Salt to taste

- Bring water and chicken to a boil  lower fire to medium and simmer for 15 mins

- Scoop put chicken and let it cool slightly before removing the bones shredding the meat

- Add the soup ingredients to the stock and simmer on medium heat for further 15 mins. Reduce fire to lowest heat

- Dissolve cornflour in water (slurry)

- Beat the eggs lightly and add in slurry. Mix well.

- Add egg slurry mixture by drizzling it slowly into the soup while stirring it at the same time

- Add in shredded chicken

- Season with salt  pepper and sesame oil
